OL,3,CAndy Burnham to cut business rates by
OL,4,C20% for pubs, clubs and music venues
OL,6,FOn Thursday, 120 UK-based
OL,7,Fmillionaires, including broadcaster
OL,8,Fand ex-footballer Gary Lineker, called
OL,9,Fon the new prime minister to impose
OL,10,Fhigher taxes on their wealth in an
OL,11,Fopen letter.
OL,13,FThe "Proud to Pay" letter to the PM,
OL,14,Forganised by the Patriotic
OL,15,FMillionaires UK campaign group, said
OL,16,Fmoney raised from higher taxes on
OL,17,Fwealth could be used to reduce
OL,18,Finequality, support public
OL,19,Finfrastructure, and back small
OL,20,Fbusinesses.
OL,26,@uD@EOUuD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784830712
OL,3,CAndy Burnham to cut business rates by
OL,4,C20% for pubs, clubs and music venues
OL,6,FIt reads: "We want you to tax us. We
OL,7,Fcan afford it.
OL,9,F"We're not talking about higher taxes
OL,10,Fon those who get up and go to work for
OL,11,Ftheir income every day, but on the
OL,12,Fvery richest whose income is derived
OL,13,Ffrom the wealth they hold."
OL,15,FLineker said of the letter: "Paying
OL,16,Fyour fair share is a basic British
OL,17,Fvalue, but so many ordinary people are
OL,18,Falready paying more than they can
OL,19,Fafford.
OL,26,@nD@KOUqD@AOUuD@[O]wD@]OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1784830712
OL,3,CAndy Burnham to cut business rates by
OL,4,C20% for pubs, clubs and music venues
OL,6,F"Our richest people can do more and
OL,7,Fmost want to. Our fantastic country
OL,8,Fdeserves all of us to get behind it."
OL,10,F"I'm proud to stand with people across
OL,11,Fthe UK who want to live in a more
OL,12,Fequal society," he added.
OL,14,FOther signatories include crime writer
OL,15,FVal McDermid, musician and songwriter
OL,16,FBrian Eno, former chairman of Greggs
OL,17,FIan Gregg, economist Gary Stevenson
OL,18,Fand investor Julia Davies.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUtD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
